### 3. Configuration: Roles, Permissions, Invitation Flow

#### Default Roles

The plugin comes with three built-in roles: `owner`, `admin`, and `member`.

#### Access Control Statements (defaultStatements)

```typescript
const defaultStatements = {
  organization: ["update", "delete"],
  member: ["create", "update", "delete"],
  invitation: ["create", "cancel"],
  team: ["create", "update", "delete"],
  ac: ["create", "read", "update", "delete"],
} as const;
```

#### Built-in Role Permissions

- **`ownerAc`**: Has all permissions on all resources
- **`adminAc`**: Has all permissions on all resources (same as owner by default)
- **`memberAc`**: Limited permissions (configurable)

#### Custom Roles

```typescript
import { organization } from "better-auth/plugins";
import { defaultAc } from "better-auth/plugins/organization/access";

organization({
  ac: defaultAc,  // or a custom AccessControl instance
  roles: {
    owner: defaultAc.newRole({
      organization: ["update", "delete"],
      member: ["create", "update", "delete"],
      invitation: ["create", "cancel"],
    }),
    admin: defaultAc.newRole({
      organization: ["update"],
      member: ["create", "update", "delete"],
      invitation: ["create", "cancel"],
    }),
    member: defaultAc.newRole({
      // minimal permissions
    }),
    // Add custom roles:
    viewer: defaultAc.newRole({
      // read-only, no write permissions
    }),
  },
  creatorRole: "owner",  // Role assigned to organization creator (default: "owner")
});
```

#### Invitation Configuration

```typescript
organization({
  // Invitation link expiry (default: 48 hours, in seconds)
  invitationExpiresIn: 48 * 60 * 60,

  // Max invitations per org (default: 100)
  invitationLimit: 100,

  // Cancel pending invitations when re-inviting same email (default: false)
  cancelPendingInvitationsOnReInvite: false,

  // Require email verification to accept/reject (default: false)
  requireEmailVerificationOnInvitation: false,

  // Send invitation email callback
  sendInvitationEmail: async (data, request) => {
    // data.id - invitation ID
    // data.email - invitee email
    // data.role - assigned role
    // data.organization - the org
    // data.invitation - full invitation object
    // data.inviter - member who invited + user data
    const url = `https://yourapp.com/organization/accept-invitation?id=${data.id}`;
    await sendEmail(data.email, "Invitation", `Join: ${url}`);
  },
});
```

**Important**: Better-auth does NOT generate invitation URLs. You must construct the URL using the invitation ID and direct users to your frontend, which then calls `acceptInvitation` with that ID.

