### 6. Getting the Active Organization from a Session/Request

#### Server-side (API routes)

On the server, the session's `activeOrganizationId` is available directly from the session object:

```typescript
// Using auth.api.getSession or equivalent:
const session = await auth.api.getSession({ headers: request.headers });
const activeOrgId = session?.session.activeOrganizationId;
// Can be null/undefined if no org is active
```

Using the server-side API methods directly:

```typescript
// Get the full organization with members and invitations
const fullOrg = await auth.api.getFullOrganization({
  headers: request.headers,
  query: {
    // If omitted, uses activeOrganizationId from session
    organizationId: "specific-org-id",
    // or
    organizationSlug: "my-org",
  },
});

// Get the active member (current user's membership in active org)
const activeMember = await auth.api.getActiveMember({
  headers: request.headers,
});
// Returns: { id, organizationId, userId, role, createdAt }
```

**Most endpoints default to `activeOrganizationId` from the session** when `organizationId` is not explicitly provided in the request body/query. This is visible throughout the source:

```javascript
// Pattern used in almost every endpoint:
const organizationId = ctx.body.organizationId || session.session.activeOrganizationId;
```

#### Client-side

```typescript
// Imperative call
const { data: fullOrg } = await authClient.organization.getFullOrganization();

// Set an organization as active
await authClient.organization.setActive({
  organizationId: "org-id",
  // or
  organizationSlug: "my-org-slug",
});

// Unset active organization (pass null)
await authClient.organization.setActive({
  organizationId: null,
});

// Reactive stores (auto-update)
// In React:
const { data: activeOrg, isPending, error } = authClient.useActiveOrganization();
// activeOrg includes: id, name, slug, logo, metadata, createdAt, members[], invitations[]

const { data: activeMember } = authClient.useActiveMember();
// activeMember: { id, organizationId, userId, role, createdAt }
```

