### POST Create Organization Invitation

Source: https://www.better-auth.com/llms.txt/docs/plugins/organization

Send an invitation to a user to join an organization with a specified role. Supports role assignment, resending invitations, and optional team assignment. Requires proper email configuration for invitation delivery.

```APIDOC
## POST /organization/invite

### Description
Sends an invitation email to a user to join an organization. The invited user will receive an email with an invitation link. Once accepted, they will be added to the organization with the specified role.

### Method
POST

### Endpoint
/organization/invite

### Parameters
#### Request Body
- **email** (string) - Required - The email address of the user to invite (e.g., "example@gmail.com")
- **role** (string | string[]) - Required - The role(s) to assign to the user. Can be "admin", "member", or "owner"
- **organizationId** (string) - Optional - The organization ID to invite the user to. Defaults to the active organization
- **resend** (boolean) - Optional - Resend the invitation email if the user is already invited (default: false)
- **teamId** (string) - Optional - The team ID to invite the user to

### Request Example
```json
{
  "email": "example@gmail.com",
  "role": "member",
  "organizationId": "org-id",
  "resend": true,
  "teamId": "team-id"
}
```

### Client Side Example
```ts
const { data, error } = await authClient.organization.inviteMember({
  email: "example@gmail.com",
  role: "member",
  organizationId: "org-id",
  resend: true,
  teamId: "team-id"
});
```

### Server Side Example
```ts
const data = await auth.api.createInvitation({
  body: {
    email: "example@gmail.com",
    role: "member",
    organizationId: "org-id",
    resend: true,
    teamId: "team-id"
  },
  headers: await headers()
});
```

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
- **invitationId** (string) - The ID of the created invitation
- **email** (string) - The email address of the invited user
- **role** (string) - The assigned role
- **organizationId** (string) - The organization ID

### Important Notes
- If the user is already a member of the organization, the invitation will be canceled
- If the user is already invited and resend is not set to true, the invitation will not be sent again
- If cancelPendingInvitationsOnReInvite is set to true, previous invitations will be canceled when re-inviting
- Requires sendInvitationEmail to be configured in the Better Auth instance
- This endpoint requires session cookies for authentication
```

--------------------------------

### Create Organization Invitation - Server Side

Source: https://www.better-auth.com/llms.txt/docs/plugins/organization

Server-side API call to create an organization invitation. Requires session cookies for authentication and accepts email, role, organizationId, resend flag, and optional teamId parameters.

```typescript
const data = await auth.api.createInvitation({
    body: {
        email: "example@gmail.com",
        role: "member",
        organizationId: "org-id", // optional
        resend: true, // optional
        teamId: "team-id", // optional
    },
    // This endpoint requires session cookies.
    headers: await headers()
});
```

--------------------------------

### List Organization Invitations - Client and Server

Source: https://www.better-auth.com/llms.txt/docs/plugins/organization

List all invitations for a given organization. The `organizationId` parameter is optional; if not provided, defaults to the user's active organization. Supports both client and server implementations.

```typescript
const { data, error } = await authClient.organization.listInvitations({
    organizationId: "organization-id",
});
```

```typescript
const data = await auth.api.listInvitations({
    query: {
        organizationId: "organization-id",
    },
    headers: await headers()
});
```

--------------------------------

### Set Organization-Based Client Reference

Source: https://www.better-auth.com/llms.txt/docs/plugins/oauth-provider

Configure OAuth clients to be tied to an organization using the activeOrganizationId from the session. This ensures clients are properly associated with organizations when using the organization plugin. The clientReference function receives the session and should return the organization ID or undefined.

```typescript
oauthProvider({
  clientReference: ({ session }) => {
    return (session?.activeOrganizationId as string | undefined) ?? undefined;
  },
})
```

--------------------------------

### Configure Initial Active Organization with BetterAuth Database Hook (TypeScript)

Source: https://www.better-auth.com/llms.txt/docs/plugins/organization

This configuration snippet demonstrates how to use BetterAuth's `databaseHooks` to automatically set an initial active organization when a new session is created. It shows how to implement custom logic within the `session.create.before` hook to determine and assign the `activeOrganizationId`.

```ts
export const auth = betterAuth({
  databaseHooks: {
    session: {
      create: {
        before: async (session) => {
          // Implement your custom logic to set initial active organization
          const organization = await getInitialOrganization(session.userId);
          return {
            data: {
              ...session,
              activeOrganizationId: organization?.id
            }
          };
        }
      }
    }
  }
});
```

### Configure BetterAuth with Organization Plugin (TypeScript)

Source: https://www.better-auth.com/llms.txt/docs/plugins/organization

This snippet demonstrates how to integrate the organization plugin into your `better-auth` configuration file (`auth.ts`). It imports the `organization` plugin and adds it to the `plugins` array during the `betterAuth` initialization. This setup enables organization management features on the server side.

```ts
import { betterAuth } from "better-auth"
import { organization } from "better-auth/plugins"

export const auth = betterAuth({
    plugins: [ // [!code highlight]
        organization() // [!code highlight]
    ] // [!code highlight]
})
```

--------------------------------

### Configure Better Auth Organization Plugin Schema in TypeScript

Source: https://www.better-auth.com/llms.txt/docs/plugins/organization

This snippet demonstrates how to customize the schema for the `organization` plugin in `better-auth`. It shows how to remap table and field names, and add new custom fields to the `organization` table, defining their type, input capability, and required status.

```ts
const auth = betterAuth({
  plugins: [
    organization({
      schema: {
        organization: {
          modelName: "organizations", //map the organization table to organizations
          fields: {
            name: "title", //map the name field to title
          },
          additionalFields: {
            // Add a new field to the organization table
            myCustomField: {
              type: "string",
              input: true,
              required: false,
            },
          },
        },
      },
    }),
  ],
});
```

--------------------------------

